Female genitalia (
Fig. 18
). Antrum somewhat funnel-shaped, sclerotized only in its proximal part; ductus bursae long, slightly broadening towards the corpus bursae, evenly sclerotized; corpus bursae very small for the genus, about the same length as the ductus, oval, membranous, with a small, rounded diverticulum connected between the ductus and corpus bursae by a short, thin tube, with ductus seminalis set medio-proximally on corpus bursae; signum a rather small, rounded patch of symmetrically arranged, inwardly directed spicules.
